contents.author: Soju | X
contents.content:
The official LFG site for @ZeusNetworkHQ is live!

Link: https://lfg.jup.ag/zeus
Launch Time:Thursday, April 4, 2024 5:00 PM
Support: ⁠lfg-support 

Learn more about Zeus: https://zeusnetwork.xyz/#network 

Check your airdrop allocation, set up your DCA/Limit orders ahead of time, and see the exact countdown to ZEUS launch. 

1% of ZEUS total supply was airdropped to Jupiter voters during the Round #1 of LFG Voting that took place. Check your airdrop allocation if you voted!

There was an additional 2% distributed to other qualifying addresses, based on the criteria here: https://medium.com/@zeus-network/zeus-token-launch-and-airdrop-claiming-on-jupiter-lfg-launchpad-7e5528768f44 

Zeus is the first LFG project that Jupiter is launching, and we are very excited to share this milestone with them and the Jupiverse community.

See you on 4/4! 

@everyone

PSA: This airdrop is not part of Active Staking Rewards (ASR), the ASR distribution will take place in July

contents.author: Soju | X
contents.content:
The CWG Budget Vote has ended! 

After 3 days of voting, the DAO vote for the latest CWG budget proposal has settled at 75% for, 19% against and 6% abstain. 
Thanks to all the catdets that came through!

This result makes the Core Working Group the first Jupiter Working Group!

There are many learnings and insights from passionate community discussions in the past few days. 

The CWG will review improvements to the voting process in a post to https://jupresear.ch/ later tomorrow, alongside a town hall later this week.

Read some initial thoughts and changes from the CWG here: https://twitter.com/KEMOS4BE/status/1774651284337140197

contents.author: Soju | X
contents.content:
The vote to fund the very first Jupiter working group is live!

This vote will be crucial in setting the precedent for working groups to come, to help drive forward the vision of the Jupiverse. Over the last week the Core Working Group has spent time engaged in community discussions and had a robust back and forth with the community to finalize their budget proposal.

Cast your vote here: https://vote.jup.ag/proposal/5N9UbMGzga3SL8Rq7qDZCGfZX3FRDUhgqkSY2ksQjg8r

Go out there and make your voice heard!

Outline of Proposal Details: https://www.jupresear.ch/t/proposal-core-working-group-budget/12689
CWG Clip at the Planetary Call: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4lUAszogT5c 
Meow interviews the CWG: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=boBGcPAKci0

As a reminder, participating in votes gives you rewards, no matter the outcome or the option you choose.
Go out there and vote, catdets! Make your voice heard!

We've just shipped three significant updates to Kamino Lend and Multiply @everyone

The update delivers improved transparency and UX to Multiply & Lending users:

Interest Earned

You can now see your interest earned for any lending position, live in the Kamino Lend interface

Multiply Price Impact

Live price impact data has now been built into the Kamino UI, providing transparent price impact estimates across all Multiply transactions

We will be rolling out these price impact estimates across our entire product suite, including:

Multiply
Repaying debt with collateral (coming soon)
Long/Short
Liquidity Vaults

Multiply positions are now substantially safer - as result of a recent oracle infrastructure update
